name: The third incarnation. Bird.
description:
My soul really liked the feeling of flying. In the next life I was born a peregrine falcon. It wasn't an easy life. There hasn't been enough food since childhood.

At first, I was hungry so much that I had to get out of my shell and loudly tell my parents about it. To hear your voice is a real miracle. This is what my soul has been deprived of for so long.

Dad fed me meat. By the irony of the universe, it was often cormorant meat.

I had a brother. It hatched a little later, was weaker and smaller. He also got less food. Nevertheless, we grew up together, made our first flight together, hunted together.

Then we had our own families. We met rarely-usually on the hunt. There were difficult times, we had to compete for food for ourselves and offspring.

One day, after a long search, I found a hare and killed it. At the same moment, death overtook me. My brother found no other way out. The hare went to feed his offspring, and I was dragged away by insects…
